WEBVTT

00:00:00.350 --> 00:00:08.281
Welcome to WaschZeit. Sign in with your personal email address

00:00:08.281 --> 00:00:16.212
and password. In Settings, check your name, language and notification

00:00:16.212 --> 00:00:23.350
preferences. Your bookings always remain assigned to your apartment.

00:00:24.350 --> 00:00:31.293
The weekly calendar helps you find a suitable available

00:00:31.293 --> 00:00:38.236
time quickly. The monthly view shows the shared laundry

00:00:38.236 --> 00:00:45.179
schedule and supports longer-term planning. Past, occupied or blocked

00:00:45.179 --> 00:00:51.350
times are clearly marked and cannot be booked.

00:00:52.350 --> 00:00:59.945
To book a laundry package, first choose a day and an

00:00:59.945 --> 00:01:07.540
available time slot. Then select a washing machine and add a

00:01:07.540 --> 00:01:15.136
suitable drying room or tumbler if needed. The app checks all

00:01:15.136 --> 00:01:21.350
house rules before saving the package as one transaction.

00:01:22.350 --> 00:01:29.100
My Bookings shows your upcoming appointments in chronological order.

00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:35.850
You can see the machine, room, date and time

00:01:35.850 --> 00:01:42.600
slot for each booking. You may only change your

00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:49.350
own bookings; bookings made by other apartments remain protected.

00:01:50.350 --> 00:01:56.600
If you finish early, release the machine or room

00:01:56.600 --> 00:02:02.850
you no longer need. Other residents can then receive

00:02:02.850 --> 00:02:09.100
a neutral notice about the newly available time. Cancelling

00:02:09.100 --> 00:02:15.350
instead removes your future booking completely before it starts.

00:02:16.350 --> 00:02:23.594
The notification center collects current information, such as a washing machine

00:02:23.594 --> 00:02:30.838
released early. Your personal filters determine which resource types and time

00:02:30.838 --> 00:02:38.082
slots interest you. Your own releases and notices that are no

00:02:38.082 --> 00:02:43.350
longer valid are not offered as bookable opportunities.

00:02:44.350 --> 00:02:50.600
If a machine or room does not work correctly, create

00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:56.850
a factual issue report. Select the affected resource and briefly

00:02:56.850 --> 00:03:03.100
describe what you observed. The house administrator then handles the

00:03:03.100 --> 00:03:09.350
technical process and decides whether the resource must be blocked.

00:03:10.350 --> 00:03:17.107
In App and Device, you can create a short-lived QR

00:03:17.107 --> 00:03:23.864
code for another household member. That person receives an individual

00:03:23.864 --> 00:03:30.620
sign-in but is assigned to the same apartment. Administrator permissions

00:03:30.620 --> 00:03:35.350
are never transferred through this QR code.

00:03:36.350 --> 00:03:42.600
Help and Rules lets you review the most important workflows

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:48.850
at any time. Security and Data explains what information is

00:03:48.850 --> 00:03:55.100
stored and which rights you have. When using a shared

00:03:55.100 --> 00:04:01.350
or unfamiliar device, always end your session by signing out.
